trans-unit.source: This class provides helpers that the Visual Basic compiler uses to do the work for the [Like Operator](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
It is not meant to be called directly from your code.
Performs binary or text string comparison given two objects.
This helper method is not meant to be called directly from your code.
For more information, see [Option Compare Statement](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
The string to compare.
The string against which `Source` is being compared.
A <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref> enumeration specifying whether or not to use text comparison.
If <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref>, this method uses text comparison; if <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref>, this method uses binary comparison.
A <xref uid="langword_csharp_Boolean" name="Boolean" href=""></xref> value indicating whether the strings match.
Returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_True" name="True" href=""></xref> if the strings match; otherwise <xref uid="langword_csharp_False" name="False" href=""></xref>.
Performs binary or text string comparison given two strings.
This helper method is not meant to be called directly from your code.
For more information, see [Option Compare Statement](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
The string to compare.
The string against which `Source` is being compared.
A <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref> enumeration specifying whether or not to use text comparison.
If <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref>, this method uses text comparison; if <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod"></xref>, this method uses binary comparison.
A <xref uid="langword_csharp_Boolean" name="Boolean" href=""></xref> value indicating whether the strings match.
Returns <xref uid="langword_csharp_True" name="True" href=""></xref> if the strings match; otherwise <xref uid="langword_csharp_False" name="False" href=""></xref>.
